        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">What Santa Ana Fire Department Inspectors Look For</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">The Santa Ana Fire Department checks fire extinguisher compliance during routine commercial property inspections. Most common violations cited in Santa Ana:</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 mb-8"><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Expired inspection tags on restaurant extinguishers — high F&B turnover in Santa Ana leads to missed annual service windows between tenant changes</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Missing Class K extinguishers in commercial kitchens — the most common violation in Santa Ana's dense restaurant district</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Wrong extinguisher class for hazard — ABC units in locations requiring Class K coverage</span></div><div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 bg-red-light rounded-lg border border-red-200"><span class="text-red-brand font-bold flex-shrink-0">!</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Obstructed extinguisher access — storage blocking units in busy commercial kitchen and retail environments</span></div></div>

